<font color="#0080ff">www.</font>addic7ed<font color="#0080ff">.com</font>

02:03.899 --> 02:07.936
♪♪

02:07.937 --> 02:15.002
♪♪

02:15.027 --> 02:18.190
[DOORBELL RINGS]

02:19.627 --> 02:22.661
The D.A.'s phone. And possibly
some of the D.A.'s blood.

02:25.794 --> 02:27.460
Morning, Carmen.

02:27.461 --> 02:29.793
Good morning, Señor Ruskin.

02:29.818 --> 02:32.369
I'll be joining the governor in an hour.

02:32.394 --> 02:34.701
God, what does a man wear
to an execution?

02:35.094 --> 02:37.626
Could you bring me a white shirt
from the laundry?

02:37.627 --> 02:43.226
♪♪

02:43.227 --> 02:48.760
♪♪

02:48.761 --> 02:50.127
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

02:52.227 --> 02:54.160
- RUSKIN: Hello?
- COLLEEN: <i> Richard.</i>

02:56.294 --> 02:57.576
What was that?

02:57.646 --> 02:58.894
Surprised?

02:58.895 --> 03:00.126
Your boys were sure surprised

03:00.127 --> 03:02.493
when I blew them into charcoal
with their own grenade.

03:02.494 --> 03:05.626
- [CELLPHONE RINGS]
- [GASPS]

03:05.627 --> 03:07.893
- Send Carmen home.
- Come on.

03:07.894 --> 03:09.293
[INTERCOM BEEPS]

03:09.294 --> 03:11.126
Carmen, you know what?

03:11.127 --> 03:12.860
You've been working like a demon.

03:12.861 --> 03:15.960
Why don't you take Ellie
to the movies today?

03:15.961 --> 03:16.827
[BEEPS]

03:16.828 --> 03:18.837
Have your people take the...

03:19.161 --> 03:21.393
item from where it is...

03:21.394 --> 03:23.226
quietly and amicably...

03:23.227 --> 03:25.626
and put it somewhere more secure.

03:25.627 --> 03:27.793
♪♪

03:27.794 --> 03:30.126
CARMEN: See you tomorrow, Señor Ruskin!

03:30.127 --> 03:31.293
[DOOR CLOSES]

03:31.294 --> 03:33.726
[GRUNTS]

03:33.727 --> 03:36.460
Where's Serena, huh?!

03:36.461 --> 03:38.293
What are you gonna do?
Cut off my fingers?

03:38.294 --> 03:39.860
Bone, tendons.

03:39.861 --> 03:41.193
That's gonna be an awful lot of cutting,

03:41.194 --> 03:42.926
and I don't think
you got the guts to do it.

03:42.927 --> 03:44.226
Oh, you're right... I don't.

03:44.227 --> 03:45.726
She does.

03:45.727 --> 03:47.886
You took my daughter.

03:48.227 --> 03:49.493
Where's Serena?

03:49.494 --> 03:50.519
[BREATHING RAGGEDLY]

03:50.544 --> 03:51.661
I-I-I don't know.

03:51.662 --> 03:52.978
[SCOFFS]

03:53.003 --> 03:55.831
How'd you make my brother
confess to the other two murders, huh?

03:56.027 --> 03:58.380
Hmm?

03:58.623 --> 04:00.655
Told him that if he didn't...

04:00.727 --> 04:02.026
his mother and Ruby would die.

04:02.027 --> 04:04.052
Do it.

04:04.861 --> 04:06.026
[GRUNTS]

04:06.027 --> 04:08.160
[BOTH SCREAM]

04:08.161 --> 04:10.560
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

04:10.561 --> 04:11.993
Where's Serena?

04:11.994 --> 04:15.926
She's on a property owned
by the family through a shell.

04:15.927 --> 04:18.327
Costa Blanca Marine Reserve.

04:20.694 --> 04:22.326
- [BEEPS]
- Richard, I have called

04:22.327 --> 04:24.593
your office and all of your clubs.

04:24.594 --> 04:26.060
- [SIGHS]
- [BEEPS]

04:26.061 --> 04:27.626
You can't call his people yourself?

04:27.627 --> 04:29.226
No, there's a firewall.

04:29.227 --> 04:31.093
There has to be.

04:31.094 --> 04:33.193
[SIGHS] Okay.

04:33.194 --> 04:36.793
We'll go on our own.
We'll talk to Kyle, as a family.

04:36.794 --> 04:39.526
And when we have Serena,
her mother will be called.

04:39.527 --> 04:42.860
[DOOR OPENS]

04:42.861 --> 04:46.426
I'm glad I'm riding to prison
with my communications director.

04:46.427 --> 04:47.860
I could use more prep.

04:47.861 --> 04:52.360
And would you like to be on
camera with me or just watch?

04:52.361 --> 04:53.693
It's completely up to you.

04:54.630 --> 04:58.593
You know, Preston,
I don't think that Logan or I should go.

04:58.594 --> 05:00.393
You're not there
as a husband or a father.

05:00.394 --> 05:02.560
The people need to see that
the State of California

05:02.561 --> 05:05.326
is killing Danny Jackson,
not any individual.

05:05.327 --> 05:07.693
It's not unwise thinking.

05:07.694 --> 05:09.693
All right. I love you both.

05:09.694 --> 05:11.493
♪♪

05:11.494 --> 05:12.826
Love you, Dad.

05:12.827 --> 05:14.527
Think good thoughts.

05:18.594 --> 05:20.926
Okay. Two cars.

05:20.927 --> 05:23.426
After Kyle, you take Serena to the boat,

05:23.427 --> 05:25.593
and I'll go to Ruskin's.

05:25.594 --> 05:26.760
[SCOFFS]

05:26.761 --> 05:28.663
Honestly...

05:29.094 --> 05:30.693
You are worse than me.

05:30.694 --> 05:36.660
♪♪

05:36.661 --> 05:39.726
The Costa Blanca Reserve
is thousands of acres.

05:39.727 --> 05:42.326
Weeks to search.

05:42.327 --> 05:43.993
<i>These were found in her pockets.</i>

05:43.994 --> 05:45.226
<i>They're Marsh Harebell.</i>

05:45.227 --> 05:47.093
<i>Found in swamps not around here.</i>

05:47.094 --> 05:48.393
Is any of this a swamp?

05:48.394 --> 05:49.860
Some kind of marshy ground?

05:49.861 --> 05:51.360
This is pines.

05:51.361 --> 05:52.760
This is scrub.

05:52.761 --> 05:54.426
But around this lake is low and flat.

05:54.427 --> 05:55.760
It's prime swamp land.

05:55.761 --> 05:57.363
If my baby's anywhere...

05:57.661 --> 05:58.760
she's there.

05:58.761 --> 06:00.760
[BIRDS CAW]

06:00.761 --> 06:08.726
♪♪

06:08.727 --> 06:12.626
In Iraq, I saw men run
into burning buildings,

06:12.627 --> 06:15.300
storm snipers' nests.

06:15.561 --> 06:18.074
I never saw anybody
give themself up to the enemy

06:18.327 --> 06:21.300
to save a comrade like you did.

06:21.427 --> 06:22.933
You're a warrior.

06:23.135 --> 06:25.956
You deserve a warrior's honor.

06:32.094 --> 06:33.126
You stay tough.

06:33.230 --> 06:34.693
You'll get through this.

06:34.694 --> 06:37.510
I'd rather go home than wear
your stupid crown.

06:37.661 --> 06:39.826
These the flowers
you're gonna put in my grave

06:39.827 --> 06:40.993
when you kill me?

06:40.994 --> 06:42.160
What grave?

06:42.161 --> 06:43.393
The one you were digging.

06:43.394 --> 06:45.327
- That's a septic.
- What's that?

06:45.328 --> 06:46.993
♪♪

06:46.994 --> 06:50.003
It's nothing a city girl needs
to worry herself about.

06:50.970 --> 06:58.069
♪♪

06:58.094 --> 07:05.193
♪♪

07:05.194 --> 07:12.326
♪♪

07:12.327 --> 07:13.526
[CHUCKLES]

07:13.527 --> 07:19.360
♪♪

07:19.361 --> 07:20.693
Mom.

07:20.694 --> 07:23.161
[SOBBING] I didn't kill any of them.

07:23.361 --> 07:26.606
I said I did, but I di... didn't.

07:26.761 --> 07:28.693
I know that, beloved.

07:28.694 --> 07:33.675
The person who did it
isn't who Nico's going to say.

07:33.927 --> 07:35.605
It isn't.

07:35.727 --> 07:36.993
Shhh.

07:37.121 --> 07:39.246
- It isn't.
- Shhh.

07:39.295 --> 07:40.426
Beloved, shhh.

07:40.427 --> 07:42.460
[SOBS]

07:42.461 --> 07:44.960
[SNIFFLES]

07:44.961 --> 07:47.327
[SHOVEL STRIKING DIRT]

07:50.827 --> 07:52.561
All done!

07:54.861 --> 07:57.960
[CLEARS THROAT]

07:57.961 --> 07:59.627
Just like yours.

08:04.594 --> 08:05.760
What's wrong?

08:05.761 --> 08:08.260
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

08:08.261 --> 08:12.260
♪♪

08:12.261 --> 08:13.893
Get inside. Now.

08:13.894 --> 08:15.093
And you don't look out no matter what,

08:15.094 --> 08:16.493
- you hear me?
- It's stuffy in there...

08:16.494 --> 08:17.993
You do what I say! Now!

08:17.994 --> 08:20.111
Go!

08:20.494 --> 08:28.360
♪♪

08:28.361 --> 08:36.226
♪♪

08:36.227 --> 08:37.493
KYLE: What's up?

08:37.494 --> 08:39.092
I can't reach Ruskin.

08:39.094 --> 08:41.493
This place might not be safe anymore.

08:41.494 --> 08:43.260
We have to take the girls
someplace else,

08:43.260 --> 08:44.393
until it's time for her to go home.

08:44.394 --> 08:45.826
Well, tell me where,
and I'll take her there.

08:45.827 --> 08:47.693
No, she's too much of a magnet.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.326
I don't want you anywhere near this.

08:49.327 --> 08:51.494
So who takes over? Ruskin's thugs?

08:51.495 --> 08:52.693
Nobody's gonna hurt her.

08:52.694 --> 08:54.126
Just like no one was ever
gonna hurt Jesse.

08:54.127 --> 08:56.026
I have no control over acts of God.

08:56.027 --> 08:57.193
God? [SCOFFS]

08:57.194 --> 08:58.626
Yeah.

08:58.627 --> 09:01.026
Jesse meets with the DA, dies,

09:01.027 --> 09:02.293
and three days later,

09:02.294 --> 09:04.526
I'm asked to watch the DA's kid
for a few days.

09:04.527 --> 09:06.126
Something about evidence
that's bad for Logan?

09:06.127 --> 09:07.560
That evidence had nothing
to do with Jesse,

09:07.561 --> 09:08.626
and it's bad for us.

09:08.627 --> 09:10.626
It would reopen Danny Jackson's case.

09:10.627 --> 09:12.460
That's why we have to do this, okay?

09:12.461 --> 09:13.942
You're not taking her anywhere.

09:13.967 --> 09:16.599
Brother, this situation is
getting uglier by the second!

09:16.694 --> 09:20.836
I owe you my life and my freedom
a hundred times over!

09:21.194 --> 09:22.560
I'll admit it.

09:22.561 --> 09:24.593
I resented how much
Mom and Dad loved you,

09:24.594 --> 09:26.602
but when I thought you were dead,

09:26.861 --> 09:29.145
part of me died.

09:29.518 --> 09:32.043
I'm a spoiled, narcissistic
piece of dirt,

09:32.856 --> 09:34.707
but I love you,

09:35.121 --> 09:37.226
and I don't want to lose you again.

09:37.227 --> 09:40.826
♪♪

09:40.827 --> 09:42.870
Will you let us take her...

09:43.094 --> 09:44.561
and keep you safe?

09:48.785 --> 09:50.119
No.

09:51.861 --> 09:53.160
[SCREAMS]

09:53.161 --> 09:55.326
♪♪

09:55.327 --> 09:57.393
- Oh, God!
- [GRUNTING]

09:57.394 --> 09:59.226
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

09:59.227 --> 10:00.727
Nooo!

10:00.800 --> 10:01.866
Oh, God!

10:01.961 --> 10:04.836
No! [SOBBING]

10:05.494 --> 10:07.555
Oh, honey!

10:07.703 --> 10:10.902
You swore you would just get past him!

10:10.927 --> 10:12.626
- He was gonna kill me!
- Sweetheart...

10:12.627 --> 10:14.993
I'll call for help,
as soon as I'm out of here.

10:14.994 --> 10:17.460
- I'm sorry.
- The sooner we get her...

10:17.485 --> 10:20.161
[BREATHING RAGGEDLY]

10:23.627 --> 10:25.293
She met you yesterday.

10:25.294 --> 10:27.726
♪♪

10:27.727 --> 10:28.993
She knows who you are.

10:28.994 --> 10:33.626
This is the river
I did <i> not</i> want to cross.

10:33.627 --> 10:35.493
We're crossing it now.

10:35.494 --> 10:37.093
We have no choice.

10:37.094 --> 10:39.326
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

10:39.327 --> 10:42.230
Not until we have her mother and Nico.

10:42.494 --> 10:44.737
They'll want proof of life.

10:44.894 --> 10:46.226
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

10:46.227 --> 10:47.691
Baby...

10:47.827 --> 10:50.693
- I'm calling for help.
- No, you keep yourself out of it.

10:50.694 --> 10:52.993
Find Ruskin and make him
send protection.

10:52.994 --> 10:55.260
I'll call 911 as soon
as I'm on my way to the boat.

10:55.261 --> 10:57.960
I'm so sorry, baby.

10:57.961 --> 10:59.826
I'm so sorry. I love you.

10:59.827 --> 11:02.326
Mom, we win this or I die!

11:02.327 --> 11:03.493
Come on!

11:03.494 --> 11:05.260
[GRUNTING]

11:05.261 --> 11:11.594
♪♪

11:15.271 --> 11:17.732
I need you to safety, honey.

11:17.757 --> 11:19.256
Please.

11:19.257 --> 11:21.523
[VOICE BREAKING] Any way you can.

11:23.857 --> 11:26.457
You're not talking to anyone.

11:26.866 --> 11:30.421
'Cause there's no one there to talk to.

11:31.304 --> 11:33.820
You're just talking to yourself.

11:34.223 --> 11:36.423
♪♪

11:40.590 --> 11:42.189
Someone was just here.

11:42.190 --> 11:44.704
Fresh tracks headed that way.

11:45.623 --> 11:47.681
Taking her to Black Pine Cove.

11:47.906 --> 11:50.705
They find her body tomorrow morning.

11:50.957 --> 11:52.556
No, they don't.

11:52.557 --> 11:55.122
[ENGINE REVS]

11:55.123 --> 11:59.422
[GATE CREAKS]

11:59.423 --> 12:06.889
♪♪

12:06.890 --> 12:09.318
Ohh...

12:10.390 --> 12:12.348
Is that blood?

12:12.986 --> 12:15.051
Oh, God!

12:15.123 --> 12:20.256
♪♪

12:20.257 --> 12:22.355
[EXHALES SHARPLY] Oh, no.

12:22.457 --> 12:24.589
♪♪

12:24.590 --> 12:27.457
[GROANING, BREATHING RAPIDLY]

12:31.257 --> 12:33.090
[SIGHS]

12:36.190 --> 12:38.022
She's alive.

12:38.023 --> 12:40.122
[GROANS]

12:40.123 --> 12:41.189
Where is she?

12:41.190 --> 12:43.022
Logan. He took her.

12:43.023 --> 12:44.289
Where did he take her?

12:44.290 --> 12:45.956
I don't know. [SCREAMS]

12:45.957 --> 12:47.022
Where'd your brother take her?

12:47.023 --> 12:48.522
- I... [GRUNTS]
- Wait, wait, wait, Nico!

12:48.523 --> 12:51.056
Nico, Nico! Look.

12:51.422 --> 12:53.589
She must've felt safe with him.

12:53.590 --> 12:55.489
Maybe it's true. Maybe... maybe...

12:55.490 --> 12:57.489
Maybe he got hurt trying to protect her.

12:57.490 --> 13:00.456
There's only one way to save Serena

13:00.457 --> 13:02.256
and your brother.

13:02.257 --> 13:04.122
Weapon.

13:04.123 --> 13:05.123
What weapon?

13:05.124 --> 13:07.056
To save them.

13:07.057 --> 13:08.689
I was there.

13:08.690 --> 13:10.256
The night Susanna was killed.

13:10.257 --> 13:11.656
I called Logan.

13:11.657 --> 13:13.556
<i>I found that girl from the tattoo shop.</i>

13:13.557 --> 13:14.789
[ <i>FIREWORKS SHOOTING</i> ]

13:14.790 --> 13:16.389
<i>Hey, man, if you don't get here quick</i>

13:16.473 --> 13:18.341
<i>and marry her, I will.</i>

13:18.523 --> 13:21.565
[BREATHING HEAVILY]
They were at the hotel,

13:21.590 --> 13:25.247
getting high... GHB, meth,

13:25.390 --> 13:26.956
whatever they could roll into a joint.

13:26.957 --> 13:28.922
[COUGHS, GROANING]

13:28.923 --> 13:30.589
Easy.

13:30.590 --> 13:33.153
Keys... t-to the weapon.

13:33.290 --> 13:34.522
Evidence.

13:34.523 --> 13:35.922
What is it? Where is it?!

13:35.923 --> 13:39.111
[GROANING] Computer.
In the top... top cupboard.

13:39.299 --> 13:45.732
♪♪

13:45.757 --> 13:48.022
File's on the desktop.

13:48.023 --> 13:50.589
It's named "7," for July.

13:50.631 --> 13:52.689
- Huh?
- Password's "Anna."

13:52.690 --> 13:54.654
For my mother...

13:54.899 --> 13:57.032
my real mother.

13:57.033 --> 13:58.465
I lost her face,

13:58.552 --> 13:59.951
kept her name.

14:00.023 --> 14:02.645
Don't listen to this crap.
The guy's out of his mind.

14:02.857 --> 14:04.022
♪♪

14:04.023 --> 14:06.489
It's a video.

14:07.490 --> 14:08.722
Watch it.

14:08.723 --> 14:09.890
- What is it?
- Not you.

14:11.190 --> 14:13.630
Just... her.

14:14.123 --> 14:16.005
Laura.

14:16.323 --> 14:18.222
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

14:18.223 --> 14:19.756
<i>Uh, Susanna, right?</i>

14:20.814 --> 14:23.743
<i>You look like you could use some
protection in these darks woods.</i>

14:23.822 --> 14:25.321
- Don't watch.
- SUSANNA: <i> Thanks. I'm... I'm good.</i>

14:25.322 --> 14:27.721
- Do... [CHOKES] Don't...
- BLAKE: <i> Camera moves in on Logan,</i>

14:27.722 --> 14:29.521
<i>totally bummed that
his offer of protection</i>

14:29.522 --> 14:30.921
<i>has been rejected.</i>

14:30.922 --> 14:33.588
JESSE: <i>Well, we're not marauders.
We're Stanford boys.</i>

14:33.589 --> 14:34.988
<i>Just graduated,</i>

14:34.989 --> 14:36.188
<i>and we're ready to burn down the world.</i>

14:36.189 --> 14:37.588
- <i>Owww!
- [CHUCKLES]</i>

14:37.589 --> 14:40.421
<i>I'm Jesse. I'm the house troubadour.</i>

14:40.422 --> 14:41.888
<i>And I'm Jason, just tagging along</i>

14:41.889 --> 14:43.811
<i>with my big brother Blake here.</i>

14:44.089 --> 14:45.855
<i>Hitchcock makes his cameo.</i>

14:45.856 --> 14:47.255
<i>[LAUGHTER]</i>

14:47.256 --> 14:50.221
<i>Look, uh... you guys are adorable,</i>

14:50.222 --> 14:52.655
<i>but it's... it's just not
a great time, okay?</i>

14:52.656 --> 14:54.088
LOGAN: <i>Can I get a drink of water?</i>

14:54.089 --> 14:57.267
- <i>July 4th is a very dehydrating holiday.
- Hey!</i>

14:57.589 --> 14:59.221
<i>- Uh... hey, get out!</i>
- [ <i>LAUGHS</i> ]

14:59.222 --> 15:00.821
<i>Get out!</i>

15:01.356 --> 15:02.455
<i>Come on!</i>

15:02.456 --> 15:04.321
[ <i>MEN SHOUTING</i> ]

15:04.322 --> 15:06.120
<i>Can we... Hey, put that down!</i>

15:06.145 --> 15:08.522
<i>My... My boyfriend's a cop,
and I'm gonna call him, okay?</i>

15:08.523 --> 15:10.604
MEN: <i> Oooh!</i>

15:10.722 --> 15:12.991
<i>This must be your boyfriend's jacket.</i>

15:13.089 --> 15:15.888
<i>If I put this on, does that
make me your boyfriend?</i>

15:15.889 --> 15:17.888
BLAKE: <i>Ohh, the tension rises.</i>

15:17.913 --> 15:20.155
KYLE: <i>Knock it off, Logan.
I'm out. Peace.</i>

15:20.189 --> 15:21.983
<i>Hey, no.</i>

15:22.710 --> 15:25.009
<i>I'm never wrong about a vibe,</i>

15:25.222 --> 15:27.453
<i>and she put out a vibe.</i>

15:27.722 --> 15:29.588
<i>It's no fair pulling it back.</i>

15:29.589 --> 15:31.781
<i>Get off me!</i>

15:31.956 --> 15:33.221
<i>Oh, bitch wants to have fun, huh?!</i>

15:33.222 --> 15:34.521
- [ <i>SCREAMS</i> ]
<i>- Come here!</i>

15:34.522 --> 15:36.188
BLAKE: <i>Whoa, this is, like, real.</i>

15:36.189 --> 15:38.188
- [ <i>CHOKING</i> ]
- JESSE: <i> Whoa, whoa, whoa! Logan!</i>

15:38.189 --> 15:40.255
<i>Okay, okay, okay!
Okay, come on, get off of her!</i>

15:40.256 --> 15:41.494
[ <i>THUD</i> ]

15:41.519 --> 15:43.018
<i>Get off!</i>

15:43.156 --> 15:46.655
[ <i>WHEEZING, BREATHING HEAVILY</i> ]

15:46.656 --> 15:48.988
♪♪

15:48.989 --> 15:50.288
JESSE: <i> Logan, no!</i>

15:50.289 --> 15:52.688
[ <i>INDISTINCT YELLING</i> ]

15:52.689 --> 15:54.832
<i>- No, no, no!</i>
- [ <i>GRUNTS</i> ]

15:55.019 --> 15:57.555
<i>- She's still alive! We need to call 911!</i>
- [ <i>SUSANNA WHEEZING</i> ]

15:57.556 --> 15:59.855
<i>Anybody touches their phones,
and they're dead!</i>

15:59.856 --> 16:02.288
- <i>Oh, you son of a...
- No, no, no! No!</i>

16:02.289 --> 16:04.920
JASON: <i>Hey, cut that off! Cut that off!</i>

16:05.089 --> 16:06.588
<i>Turn the camera off, Blake!</i>

16:06.589 --> 16:08.205
Nico...

16:08.489 --> 16:10.555
[SOBS]

16:10.556 --> 16:15.055
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

16:15.056 --> 16:16.788
[GRUNTS] You knew!

16:16.789 --> 16:18.316
You knew and let my brother die! You knew!

16:18.341 --> 16:19.721
- Nico, Nico, Nico!
- I'm sorry!

16:19.722 --> 16:22.121
- Hold on!
- You knew! He wrecked my mother's life!

16:22.122 --> 16:23.188
- I know, I know, I know!
- You knew?!

16:23.189 --> 16:24.812
I know... I know he did all of that,

16:24.869 --> 16:25.890
and he'll pay,

16:25.999 --> 16:27.155
but he's a witness, and we need him.

16:27.156 --> 16:29.355
Listen to me. I know exactly what to do.

16:29.356 --> 16:31.255
But we have to leave this second!

16:31.256 --> 16:32.955
We have to take him with us!

16:32.956 --> 16:33.934
Get him! Now!

16:33.959 --> 16:35.725
Come on, get him!

16:35.787 --> 16:37.286
Up!

16:37.334 --> 16:39.221
Get up! Let's go!

16:39.222 --> 16:39.956
[GROANING]

16:41.122 --> 16:43.421
You said you were gonna
get help for him.

16:43.422 --> 16:44.643
You have to call 911.

16:44.734 --> 16:47.721
Didn't you ever tell a lie
to make your mother feel better?

16:48.158 --> 16:50.025
He's dead by now.

16:53.954 --> 16:55.155
KYLE: <i> Flip it over.</i>

16:55.156 --> 16:56.855
<i>Push back. Twist.</i>

16:56.856 --> 17:03.055
♪♪

17:03.056 --> 17:04.688
Cut that out!

17:04.689 --> 17:05.944
Hey!

17:06.095 --> 17:07.554
Hey!

17:08.622 --> 17:09.788
[GROANS]

17:09.789 --> 17:10.789
[TIRES SCREECH]

17:10.790 --> 17:12.088
[ENGINE REVS]

17:12.089 --> 17:15.155
[METAL CRUNCHES]

17:15.156 --> 17:17.189
♪♪

